column197: NEARBY SHIP DRONE CONTROL SYSTEM DAMAGE

column11: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: Drones -  If you're struggling against enemy Drones, target the Drone System to temporarily disable them.
As you wait for the FTL drive to charge, you half expect to be ambushed at any moment. However, no attack comes...
You see a number of derelict ships near this beacon. After a short time you hear the tell-tale sounds of a teleporter and shouts coming from within the ship. You've been boarded!
You search the ship and discover that its cargo was new military-grade weaponry! It was somehow undamaged in the fight and can easily be mounted on the ship.
You make the colonists teleport the supplies to your ship. It's nothing more than building construction supplies. Oh well, scrap is scrap.
You take a hopeful trip to the Clone Bay, and to your relief a clone is already prepared for the lost crewmember.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

You use your ion weaponry to disable the gun long enough for their repair crews to fix it. They message you, I've never seen a weapon like that before! Thanks for your help. Please accept this reward.
The space station here has a traveling merchant who shows you his wares.
column12: Drone: COMBAT BEAM 2, BATTLE, COMBAT BEAM, System: teleporter, battery, mind,

column11: The ship appears to have been transporting prisoners. Unfortunately they were all killed in the battle. You salvage what you can.
The station was apparently designed to outfit Rebel ships with Drone Systems. You find a functioning Schematic.
This sector was the site of many major battles between the Federation and Rebel fleets. Strangely, there's very little evidence of those battles remaining...
The Rockman ship jumped away during the battle, but it left much of its hull and spare parts floating behind - you salvage what you can, and prepare to jump.
They are grateful for your contribution and offer you some Lanius equipment that they were previously studying.
This sector has become increasingly dangerous for friends of the Federation. I think my crew can patch up some of your hull damage as thanks.
You release the material out of the airlock and the Lanius quickly collect it and start melting it down. They are grateful for your assistance and send over a ship augmentation.

This beacon is bustling with activity. It looks like some merchants decided to capitalize on the fact that dozens of refugee ships are using this location to recharge their FTL drives. You browse their wares.
column12: Weapon: BEAM HULL, LASER HEAVY 1, LASER BURST 2 A, System: medbay, cloaking, mind, Drone: BATTLE, DRONE SHIELD, ANTI DRONE,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a collection of useful scrap material.

The Slugs reluctantly thank you for your help, protest they had the whole situation under control, attempt to make you pay for them helping you, and an hour later, finally relent and give you some supplies.

After your skirmish the fighting dies down and you're contacted by the planetary defense team. Sorry you got caught up in that fight, stranger. No matter how many of these monsters we blow out of the sky they just keep coming. We can patch up your ship for you.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Thank you for your business, no refunds!
This sector was the site of many major battles between the Federation and Rebel fleets. Strangely, there's very little evidence of those battles remaining...
You arrive at an empty space station, no doubt abandoned due to the Lanius threat. Life signatures are detected at the ship depot and you spot a few crude signs stating Everything Must Go!
column12: Weapon: LASER CHAINGUN 2, LASER CHARGEGUN, BOMB 1, Drone: DEFENSE 1, DEFENSE 2, BOARDER, Crew: Zoltan, Human, Slug, System: medbay, cloaking, mind,

column11: You happen upon an abandoned mining site. A few mining drones were left behind and could be repurposed.
The competitor gone, you investigate the debris, but it looks as if the Lanius harvested much of it before you arrived.

You stumble across a badly damaged Lanius craft. It jumps away as soon as it sees you. Looking around the area, you discover a number of destroyed Rebel automated ships. It must have been quite the fight. You scrap what remains.

The Mantis hiss and click, angry at being saved, and angry at themselves for needing to be saved. They part ways with some scrap metal that is no longer attached to their hull and a few missiles they can no longer use.

A trading depot is set up near the beacon. A surprising number of military ships guard the station. You pick up an advertisement on a wide band channel, Ship parts, repairs, refueling, souvenirs - we got it all. Check out the only store not afraid of scavengers this side of Omacron 6.
column12: System: medbay, cloaking, mind, Crew: Human, Engi, Human,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

After your skirmish the fighting dies down and you're contacted by the planetary defense team. Sorry you got caught up in that fight, stranger. No matter how many of these monsters we blow out of the sky they just keep coming. We can patch up your ship for you.
After the exchange is complete they leave without a word.

An image of some weak and hungry humans comes onto your screen. Those metal bastards think they can just absorb half of our engines and leave us here to die? I hope you understand the need to take your ship by force.
You thank them but prepare to move on.
At one point this was one of the most commonly traveled sectors. Knowing that, the Rebels have stationed a number of fleets here. Be careful.

There are no other ships near this beacon, however you detect a small communication relay. You tap into it without a problem; there is no encryption. Most of the chatter revolves around troop and fleet movements, not particularly interesting.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The station was either abandoned or stripped clean. It seems to have lain unused for quite some time. You find nothing useful.
You receive generic advertisements from a nearby public ship-yard. It seems they are willing to work on any ship, not only those of Rebel hue.
column12: System: medbay, teleporter, mind, Drone: REPAIR, DEFENSE 1, DEFENSE 2,

column11: You search the remains of the ship, but only come across blueprints and debris from broken machinery. A shame, but you take what scrap you can salvage.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship breaks apart and you feel relief in the knowledge that you will hopefully still be one step ahead of the fleet.

Your crew valiantly keeps the fire at bay long enough to allow some of the scientists to escape, but it appears to be a losing battle. Before long you order the retreat. The few scientists they were able to save are distraught but grateful. You'll drop them off at the next station.
The mercenary ship masks its jump signature to mimic your own and then jumps off in the opposite direction. This should keep the Rebels guessing.
Their ship breaks apart and you are relieved to know that you are still one step ahead of the fleet.
Thank you, this will help greatly.
The Zoltan patrol their borders but let you pass when you ID as Federation. Let's hope they won't be so courteous to the Rebels.

Your crew calmly lines up for the Zoltans to take their readings. After a short time, the process is done. They contact you, Thank you for your participation in our study. Please accept these small cakes made from stiff dough as well as some scrap.
A Zoltan shipyard is stationed at this beacon. You admire the display of hundreds of glowing Zoltan performing delicate exterior work on a massive transport ship.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

They finish: Please, spread the word of enlightenment to those that have not heard. Once you have, contact our brethren. They transmit coordinates of their so-called brethren. Added a quest marker to your map!
A human ship hails: My friends! Please, there is nothing I don't have, and there is nothing worth wanting that I can't get. Why not take a look around my shop?

column11: Although your methods are crude and most certainly ineffective, it is clear you took our previous meeting to heart. If your ship represents the Federation's willingness to adapt we shall do what we can to aid in their fight. This technology should aid your quest.
column71: AUTO COOLDOWN, DEFENSE SCRAMBLER, ENERGY SHIELD

column11: You overhear one group discussing a newly discovered planet yet to have first contact, and note down its location. Added a quest marker to your map!

column11: You arrive near the Federation Base to find the bulk of their fleet skirmishing with Rebel forces. You hang back near the far side of the moon to avoid the conflict. There's not much you can do to help in that battle, and your mission holds the key to turn the tide of the war. You prepare to face the Flagship.
